;'''Piano''' (noun)
:Short for '''Pianoforte'''.  A keyboard musical instrument, usually ranging five octaves, with white and black keys. The white keys play one full tone from each other, while the black ones play a semi-tone from the adjacent white.  

;'''Piano''' (adj.)
:Soft. Used as a [[w:dynamic|dynamic]] directive in [[w:sheet music|sheet music]] in its abbreviated form, ''{p.}'', to denote lowering the volume of the music. In the pianoforte this is done by pressing the instrument's keys more lightly. 

==Etymology==

;'''Pianoforte'''
:Italian ''Piano'' (soft) + ''forte'' (strong). So named because older keyboard instruments, notably the [[harpsichord]] and the [[clavier]], could not produce varied volumes.  

